Example how to compile, install, and access a loadable kernel module

[read the documentation in 'kernelModule.pdf']

0) make your own 'hello' kernel module and name it 'hello.c'
1) compile your dummy kernel module in 'hello.c' by typing "make"
2) connect to your LART through minicom
3) download 'hello.ko' and the 'setup' script
4) execute the 'setup' script by typing "sh setup"
5) insert the kernel module by typing "insmod hello.ko", which yields the
   message 'Lart kernel module inserted'
6) read data from the /dev/lart file, for example, by typing "cat /dev/lart"
